tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE WorkoutRoutine (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  exercise_name VARCHAR(255),
  sets INT,
  reps INT,
  weight FLOAT,
  date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE workout_progress (
    progress_id INT,
    routine_id INT,
    progress_date DATE,
    calories_burned INT,
    workout_intensity VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE workout_progress (
    progress_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    workout_id INT,
    progress_date DATE,
    progress_weight DECIMAL(10, 2),
    progress_notes TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE workout_stats (
    stats_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    workout_id INT,
    total_sets INT,
    total_reps INT,
    avg_weight_lifted DECIMAL(10, 2)
);

CREATE TABLE workout_log (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  workout_id INT,
  exercise_id INT,
  sets INT,
  reps INT
);

CREATE TABLE workouts (
   workout_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   date DATE NOT NULL,
   exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
   sets INT NOT NULL,
   reps INT NOT NULL,
   weight DECIMAL NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE exercise_logs (
   log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   workout_id INT NOT NULL,
   exercise_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
   sets_completed INT NOT NULL,
   reps_completed INT NOT NULL,
   weight_used DECIMAL NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE progress_tracking (
   tracking_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id INT NOT NULL,
   date DATE NOT NULL,
   weight DECIMAL NOT NULL,
   body_fat DECIMAL NOT NULL
);
